# Privacy Policy – DataLayer Checker BD

**Effective date:** 2026-05-11  
**Extension name:** DataLayer Checker BD — GTM & DataLayer Inspector  
**Developer:** Eiaser Hosen  
**GitHub:** https://github.com/eiaserbd

## Overview

DataLayer Checker BD is a Chrome extension built to help users inspect and debug `window.dataLayer` events for Google Tag Manager (GTM) workflows.

Your privacy is important. This policy explains what data the extension accesses, how it is used, and what control you have.

## Data We Access

The extension may access the following while you browse websites:

- `window.dataLayer` event payloads pushed on pages you visit
- Current page URL/context (used to reset capture when the page/route changes)
- User-configured settings stored in extension storage (for example, GTM workspace URL, theme preference, snapshot data)

## How Data Is Used

Data is used only to provide extension features, including:

- Real-time event capture and display in the popup
- Filtering and searching captured events
- Flat/JSON inspection views
- Copy/export/snapshot functionality
- Resetting old captures when page context changes

## Data Storage

- Data is stored locally using Chrome extension storage (`chrome.storage.local`).
- Snapshot and captured events remain in local browser storage until cleared by the user or overwritten by normal extension behavior.
- The extension does **not** require account sign-in.

## Data Sharing

- We do **not** sell your data.
- We do **not** share captured payload data with third parties.
- We do **not** transmit captured event data to our servers.

## Permissions and Why They Are Needed

- **`storage`**: Save user settings, snapshots, and event buffers locally.
- **`<all_urls>` host access**: Observe `dataLayer` events on websites where GTM/debugging is needed.
- **Content script injection**: Connect page events to the extension UI for debugging.

## User Controls

You can:

- Pause/resume event capture from the popup
- Clear buffered events
- Delete snapshots
- Uninstall the extension at any time

## Uninstall Behavior

When uninstalling, Chrome may open the configured uninstall page:
- https://bluenill.com/

## Security

We aim to keep the extension minimal and avoid unnecessary data processing.  
No hidden data collection is intended.

## Children’s Privacy

This extension is not specifically directed to children under 13.

